      "content": "<div class=\"side-by-side-layout\">\n    <div class=\"figures-row\">\n        <figure>\n            <img src=\"/static/images/courses/cmsc173/module-01/parameter_estimation_concept_left.png\" alt=\"Normal Distribution with Parameters\">\n        </figure>\n        <figure>\n            <img src=\"/static/images/courses/cmsc173/module-01/parameter_estimation_concept_right.png\" alt=\"Estimation Process\">\n        </figure>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"text-row\">\n        <div class=\"definition\">\n            <h4>Variables</h4>\n            <ul>\n                <li>$X$: Random variable</li>\n                <li>$\\theta$: True parameter</li>\n                <li>$\\hat{\\theta}$: Estimate</li>\n            </ul>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"definition\" style=\"margin-top:16px\">\n            <h4>Functions</h4>\n            <ul>\n                <li>$f(x|\\theta)$: PDF/PMF</li>\n                <li>$L(\\theta|x)$: Likelihood</li>\n            </ul>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n</div>"
    },
    {
      "id": 7,
      "title": "Understanding Moments",
      "readingTime": "1 min",
      "content": "<div class=\"side-by-side-layout\">\n    <div class=\"figures-row\">\n        <figure>\n            <img src=\"/static/images/courses/cmsc173/module-01/moments_illustration_left.png\" alt=\"First Moment - Mean\">\n        </figure>\n        <figure>\n            <img src=\"/static/images/courses/cmsc173/module-01/moments_illustration_right.png\" alt=\"Second Moment - Variance\">\n        </figure>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"text-row\">\n        <div class=\"definition\">\n            <h4>$k$-th Moment</h4>\n            $$m_k = E[X^k]$$\n        </div>\n        <ul style=\"margin-top:16px\">\n            <li>$m_1 = \\mu$ (mean)</li>\n            <li>$\\mu_2 = \\sigma^2$ (variance)</li>\n        </ul>\n    </div>\n</div>"
    },
    {
      "id": 8,
      "title": "Method of Moments: Core Idea",
      "readingTime": "1 min",
      "content": "<div class=\"callout blue\">\n    <div class=\"callout-title\"><i class=\"fa-solid fa-lightbulb\"></i> Core Principle</div>\n    <p>Match <strong>sample moments</strong> to <strong>theoretical moments</strong> to estimate parameters.</p>\n</div>\n<div class=\"card-grid\" style=\"grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);margin-top:20px\">\n    <div class=\"info-card\">\n        <div class=\"icon blue\"><i class=\"fa-solid fa-1\"></i></div>\n        <h4>Theory</h4>\n        <p>$m_k(\\theta)$</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"info-card\">\n        <div class=\"icon green\"><i class=\"fa-solid fa-2\"></i></div>\n        <h4>Sample</h4>\n        <p>$\\hat{m}_k = \\frac{1}{n}\\sum x_i^k$</p>\n    </div>\n</div>"
    },
    {
      "id": 9,
      "title": "MoM Algorithm",
      "readingTime": "1 min",
      "content": "<div class=\"side-by-side-layout\">\n    <div class=\"figures-row\">\n        <figure>\n            <img src=\"/static/images/courses/cmsc173/module-01/mom_visualization_left.png\" alt=\"MoM - Sample Moments\">\n        </figure>\n        <figure>\n            <img src=\"/static/images/courses/cmsc173/module-01/mom_visualization_right.png\" alt=\"MoM - Theoretical Moments\">\n        </figure>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"text-row\">\n        <ol style=\"margin:0\">\n            <li>Express moments: $m_k(\\theta)$</li>\n            <li>Calculate sample: $\\hat{m}_k$</li>\n            <li>Set equal: $m_k(\\theta) = \\hat{m}_k$</li>\n            <li>Solve for $\\hat{\\theta}$</li>\n        </ol>\n    </div>\n</div>"
    },
    {
      "id": 10,
      "title": "MoM: Normal Distribution",
      "readingTime": "1 min",
      "content": "<div class=\"callout blue\" style=\"margin-bottom:16px\">\n    <div class=\"callout-title\"><i class=\"fa-solid fa-chart-simple\"></i> Goal</div>\n    <p>Estimate $\\mu$ and $\\sigma^2$ for $N(\\mu, \\sigma^2)$</p>\n</div>\n<div class=\"two-col\">\n    <div>\n        <h4>Theory</h4>\n        <p>$m_1 = \\mu$</p>\n        <p>$m_2 = \\mu^2 + \\sigma^2$</p>\n    </div>\n    <div>\n        <h4>MoM Estimates</h4>\n        <p>$\\hat{\\mu} = \\bar{x}$</p>\n        <p>$\\hat{\\sigma}^2 = \\frac{1}{n}\\sum(x_i - \\bar{x})^2$</p>\n    </div>\n</div>"
    },
    {
      "id": 11,
      "title": "MoM: Poisson Distribution",
      "readingTime": "1 min",
      "content": "<div class=\"side-by-side-layout\">\n    <div class=\"figures-row\">\n        <figure>\n            <img src=\"/static/images/courses/cmsc173/module-01/mom_poisson_example_left.png\" alt=\"Poisson Distribution\">\n        </figure>\n        <figure>\n            <img src=\"/static/images/courses/cmsc173/module-01/mom_poisson_example_right.png\" alt=\"Poisson MoM Estimation\">\n        </figure>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"text-row\">\n        <div class=\"callout blue\" style=\"margin-bottom:12px\">\n            <div class=\"callout-title\"><i class=\"fa-solid fa-calculator\"></i> Poisson($\\lambda$)</div>\n            <p>Theory: $E[X] = \\lambda$</p>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"definition\">\n            <h4>MoM Estimate</h4>\n            $$\\hat{\\lambda} = \\bar{x}$$\n        </div>\n    </div>\n</div>"
    },
    {
      "id": 12,
      "title": "MoM: Gamma Distribution",
      "readingTime": "1 min",
      "content": "<div class=\"callout blue\" style=\"margin-bottom:16px\">\n    <div class=\"callout-title\"><i class=\"fa-solid fa-calculator\"></i> Gamma($\\alpha, \\beta$)</div>\n    <p>$E[X] = \\alpha\\beta$, $Var(X) = \\alpha\\beta^2$</p>\n</div>\n<div class=\"definition\">\n    <h4>MoM Estimates</h4>\n    $$\\hat{\\beta} = \\frac{\\hat{\\sigma}^2}{\\bar{x}}, \\quad \\hat{\\alpha} = \\frac{\\bar{x}^2}{\\hat{\\sigma}^2}$$\n</div>"
    },
    {
      "id": 13,
      "title": "MoM Properties",
      "readingTime": "1 min",
      "content": "<div class=\"side-by-side-layout\">\n    <div class=\"figures-row\">\n        <figure>\n            <img src=\"/static/images/courses/cmsc173/module-01/mom_properties_left.png\" alt=\"MoM Advantages\">\n        </figure>\n        <figure>\n            <img src=\"/static/images/courses/cmsc173/module-01/mom_properties_right.png\" alt=\"MoM Limitations\">\n        </figure>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"text-row\">\n        <div class=\"callout green\" style=\"margin-bottom:12px\">\n            <div class=\"callout-title\"><i class=\"fa-solid fa-check\"></i> Pros</div>\n            <p>Simple, consistent, general</p>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"callout pink\">\n            <div class=\"callout-title\"><i class=\"fa-solid fa-xmark\"></i> Cons</div>\n            <p>Not optimal, may give invalid estimates</p>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n</div>"
    },
    {
      "id": 14,
      "title": "Maximum Likelihood: Core Idea",
      "readingTime": "1 min",
      "content": "<div class=\"side-by-side-layout\">\n    <div class=\"figures-row\">\n        <figure>\n            <img src=\"/static/images/courses/cmsc173/module-01/likelihood_concept_left.png\" alt=\"Likelihood Function\">\n        </figure>\n        <figure>\n            <img src=\"/static/images/courses/cmsc173/module-01/likelihood_concept_right.png\" alt=\"Maximum Likelihood Point\">\n        </figure>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"text-row\">\n        <div class=\"callout blue\">\n            <div class=\"callout-title\"><i class=\"fa-solid fa-lightbulb\"></i> Core Principle</div>\n            <p>Find parameters that make observed data <strong>most likely</strong>.</p>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n</div>"
    },
    {
      "id": 15,
      "title": "The Likelihood Function",
      "readingTime": "1 min",
      "content": "<div class=\"side-by-side-layout\">\n    <div class=\"figures-row\">\n        <figure>\n            <img src=\"/static/images/courses/cmsc173/module-01/likelihood_concept_left.png\" alt=\"Likelihood Function\">\n        </figure>\n        <figure>\n            <img src=\"/static/images/courses/cmsc173/module-01/likelihood_concept_right.png\" alt=\"Log-Likelihood Function\">\n        </figure>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"text-row\">\n        <div class=\"definition\" style=\"margin-bottom:16px\">\n            <h4>Likelihood</h4>\n            $$L(\\theta) = \\prod_{i=1}^n f(x_i | \\theta)$$\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"definition\">\n            <h4>Log-Likelihood</h4>\n            $$\\ell(\\theta) = \\sum_{i=1}^n \\log f(x_i | \\theta)$$\n        </div>\n    </div>\n</div>"
    },
    {
      "id": 16,
      "title": "Finding the MLE",
      "readingTime": "1 min",
      "content": "<div class=\"side-by-side-layout\">\n    <div class=\"figures-row\">\n        <figure>\n            <img src=\"/static/images/courses/cmsc173/module-01/mle_visualization_left.png\" alt=\"Log-Likelihood Curve\">\n        </figure>\n        <figure>\n            <img src=\"/static/images/courses/cmsc173/module-01/mle_visualization_right.png\" alt=\"MLE Optimization\">\n        </figure>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"text-row\">\n        <div class=\"definition\">\n            <h4>MLE</h4>\n            $$\\hat{\\theta}_{MLE} = \\arg\\max_\\theta \\ell(\\theta)$$\n        </div>\n        <p style=\"margin-top:16px\"><strong>Method:</strong> Solve $\\frac{d\\ell}{d\\theta} = 0$</p>\n    </div>\n</div>"
    },
    {
      "id": 17,
      "title": "MLE: Normal Distribution",
      "readingTime": "1 min",
      "content": "<div class=\"callout blue\" style=\"margin-bottom:16px\">\n    <div class=\"callout-title\"><i class=\"fa-solid fa-chart-simple\"></i> Goal</div>\n    <p>Estimate $\\mu$ and $\\sigma^2$ for $N(\\mu, \\sigma^2)$</p>\n</div>\n<div class=\"definition\">\n    <h4>MLE Solutions</h4>\n    $$\\hat{\\mu}_{MLE} = \\bar{x}$$\n    $$\\hat{\\sigma}^2_{MLE} = \\frac{1}{n}\\sum_{i=1}^n(x_i - \\bar{x})^2$$\n</div>"
    },
    {
      "id": 18,
      "title": "MLE: Poisson Distribution",
      "readingTime": "1 min",
      "content": "<div class=\"two-col\">\n    <div>\n        <h4>Log-likelihood</h4>\n        <p>$\\ell(\\lambda) = (\\sum x_i)\\log\\lambda - n\\lambda$</p>\n        <h4 style=\"margin-top:16px\">Score</h4>\n        <p>$\\frac{d\\ell}{d\\lambda} = \\frac{\\sum x_i}{\\lambda} - n = 0$</p>\n    </div>\n    <div>\n        <div class=\"definition\">\n            <h4>MLE</h4>\n            $$\\hat{\\lambda} = \\bar{x}$$\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"callout\" style=\"margin-top:16px\">\n            <div class=\"callout-title\"><i class=\"fa-solid fa-lightbulb\"></i> Note</div>\n            <p>Same as MoM for Poisson!</p>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n</div>"
    },
    {
      "id": 19,
      "title": "MLE: Exponential Distribution",
      "readingTime": "1 min",
      "content": "<div class=\"side-by-side-layout\">\n    <div class=\"figures-row\">\n        <figure>\n            <img src=\"/static/images/courses/cmsc173/module-01/mle_exponential_left.png\" alt=\"Exponential Distribution\">\n        </figure>\n        <figure>\n            <img src=\"/static/images/courses/cmsc173/module-01/mle_exponential_right.png\" alt=\"Exponential MLE\">\n        </figure>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"text-row\">\n        <div class=\"callout blue\" style=\"margin-bottom:12px\">\n            <div class=\"callout-title\"><i class=\"fa-solid fa-calculator\"></i> Exponential($\\lambda$)</div>\n            <p>$f(x) = \\lambda e^{-\\lambda x}$</p>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"definition\">\n            <h4>MLE</h4>\n            $$\\hat{\\lambda} = \\frac{1}{\\bar{x}}$$\n        </div>\n    </div>\n</div>"
    },
    {
      "id": 20,
      "title": "MLE Properties",
      "readingTime": "1 min",
      "content": "<div class=\"side-by-side-layout\">\n    <div class=\"figures-row\">\n        <figure>\n            <img src=\"/static/images/courses/cmsc173/module-01/mle_properties_left.png\" alt=\"MLE Consistency\">\n        </figure>\n        <figure>\n            <img src=\"/static/images/courses/cmsc173/module-01/mle_properties_right.png\" alt=\"MLE Efficiency\">\n        </figure>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"text-row\">\n        <ul>\n            <li><strong>Consistent:</strong> $\\hat{\\theta} \\to \\theta$</li>\n            <li><strong>Asymptotically Normal</strong></li>\n            <li><strong>Efficient:</strong> Min variance</li>\n            <li><strong>Invariant:</strong> $g(\\hat{\\theta})$ is MLE of $g(\\theta)$</li>\n        </ul>\n    </div>\n</div>"
    },
    {
      "id": 21,
      "title": "Fisher Information",
      "readingTime": "1 min",
      "content": "<div class=\"definition\" style=\"margin-bottom:20px\">\n    <h4>Fisher Information</h4>\n    $$I(\\theta) = -E\\left[\\frac{d^2\\ell}{d\\theta^2}\\right]$$\n</div>\n<div class=\"two-col\">\n    <div>\n        <h4>Cram√©r-Rao Bound</h4>\n        <p>$Var(\\hat{\\theta}) \\geq \\frac{1}{I(\\theta)}$</p>\n    </div>\n    <div>\n        <div class=\"callout\">\n            <div class=\"callout-title\"><i class=\"fa-solid fa-lightbulb\"></i> Insight</div>\n            <p>Higher information = lower variance</p>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n</div>"
    },
    {
      "id": 22,
      "title": "Numerical MLE Methods",
      "readingTime": "1 min",
      "content": "<div class=\"side-by-side-layout\">\n    <div class=\"figures-row\">\n        <figure>\n            <img src=\"/static/images/courses/cmsc173/module-01/numerical_mle_left.png\" alt=\"Numerical Optimization\">\n        </figure>\n        <figure>\n            <img src=\"/static/images/courses/cmsc173/module-01/numerical_mle_right.png\" alt=\"Convergence\">\n        </figure>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"text-row\">\n        <div class=\"callout pink\" style=\"margin-bottom:12px\">\n            <div class=\"callout-title\"><i class=\"fa-solid fa-exclamation\"></i> When Needed</div>\n            <p>No closed-form solution</p>\n        </div>\n        <ul>\n            <li>Newton-Raphson</li>\n            <li>Gradient ascent</li>\n            <li>EM algorithm</li>\n        </ul>\n    </div>\n</div>"
    },
    {
      "id": 23,
      "title": "MoM vs MLE: Comparison",
      "readingTime": "1 min",
      "content": "<div class=\"side-by-side-layout\">\n    <div class=\"figures-row\">\n        <figure>\n            <img src=\"/static/images/courses/cmsc173/module-01/mom_vs_mle_comparison_left.png\" alt=\"MoM Estimation\">\n        </figure>\n        <figure>\n            <img src=\"/static/images/courses/cmsc173/module-01/mom_vs_mle_comparison_right.png\" alt=\"MLE Estimation\">\n        </figure>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"text-row\">\n        <table class=\"comparison-table\" style=\"font-size:13px\">\n            <thead><tr><th></th><th>MoM</th><th>MLE</th></tr></thead>\n            <tbody>\n                <tr><td>Speed</td><td>Fast</td><td>Varies</td></tr>\n                <tr><td>Efficiency</td><td>Lower</td><td>Optimal</td></tr>\n                <tr><td>Complexity</td><td>Simple</td><td>Complex</td></tr>\n            </tbody>\n        </table>\n    </div>\n</div>"
    },
    {
      "id": 24,
      "title": "Efficiency Comparison",
      "readingTime": "1 min",
      "content": "<div class=\"side-by-side-layout\">\n    <div class=\"figures-row\">\n        <figure>\n            <img src=\"/static/images/courses/cmsc173/module-01/efficiency_comparison_left.png\" alt=\"MoM Variance\">\n        </figure>\n        <figure>\n            <img src=\"/static/images/courses/cmsc173/module-01/efficiency_comparison_right.png\" alt=\"MLE Variance\">\n        </figure>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"text-row\">\n        <div class=\"definition\" style=\"margin-bottom:12px\">\n            <h4>Relative Efficiency</h4>\n            $$ARE = \\frac{Var_{MLE}}{Var_{MoM}}$$\n        </div>\n        <ul style=\"font-size:13px\">\n            <li>Normal $\\mu$: ARE = 1</li>\n            <li>Normal $\\sigma^2$: ARE = 0.5</li>\n            <li>Gamma: MLE wins</li>\n        </ul>\n    </div>\n</div>"
    },
    {
      "id": 25,
      "title": "When to Use Which?",
      "readingTime": "1 min",
      "content": "<div class=\"two-col\">\n    <div>\n        <div class=\"callout green\">\n            <div class=\"callout-title\"><i class=\"fa-solid fa-calculator\"></i> Use MoM</div>\n            <p>Quick estimates, starting values, simple distributions</p>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n    <div>\n        <div class=\"callout purple\">\n            <div class=\"callout-title\"><i class=\"fa-solid fa-chart-line\"></i> Use MLE</div>\n            <p>Optimal estimates, inference, model comparison</p>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"callout\" style=\"margin-top:20px\">\n    <div class=\"callout-title\"><i class=\"fa-solid fa-lightbulb\"></i> Pro Tip</div>\n    <p>Use MoM estimates as starting values for MLE optimization.</p>\n</div>"
    },
    {
      "id": 26,
      "title": "Application: Linear Regression",
      "readingTime": "1 min",
      "content": "<div class=\"side-by-side-layout\">\n    <div class=\"figures-row\">\n        <figure>\n            <img src=\"/static/images/courses/cmsc173/module-01/linear_regression_estimation_left.png\" alt=\"Linear Regression Data\">\n        </figure>\n        <figure>\n            <img src=\"/static/images/courses/cmsc173/module-01/linear_regression_estimation_right.png\" alt=\"Linear Regression Fit\">\n        </figure>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"text-row\">\n        <div class=\"callout blue\" style=\"margin-bottom:12px\">\n            <div class=\"callout-title\"><i class=\"fa-solid fa-chart-line\"></i> Model</div>\n            <p>$y = \\beta_0 + \\beta_1 x + \\epsilon$</p>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"definition\">\n            <h4>Estimates</h4>\n            <p>$\\hat{\\beta}_1 = \\frac{\\sum(x_i-\\bar{x})(y_i-\\bar{y})}{\\sum(x_i-\\bar{x})^2}$</p>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n</div>"
    },
    {
      "id": 27,
